=== Events ===
* In the 9th year of {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保}} ({{ill|1838 AD|ja|1838年}}), {{ill|Kōya Nagahide|ja|高野長英}} authored the work {{ill|Wuxu Dream Tale|ja|戊戌夢物語}}.
* In the 24th year of {{ill|Guangxu|ja|光緒}} ({{ill|1898 AD|ja|1898年}}), during the Qing dynasty, reforms and political upheaval known as the {{ill|Wuxu Reform|ja|戊戌の変法}} and the {{ill|Wuxu Coup|ja|戊戌の政変}} took place.

== Months of Wuxu ==
In a {{ill|Common Era|ja|西暦}} year whose final digit is 1 or 6 (i.e. when the Ten Heavenly Stems are {{ill|Xin|ja|辛}} or {{ill|Bing|ja|丙}}), the month of {{ill|September|ja|9月}} becomes the {{ill|Month (Calendar)|ja|月 (暦)|lt=Month}} of Wuxu. However, the term “month” here may refer either to the month of the {{ill|Lunisolar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar}} or to a seasonal month (from {{ill|Hanro|ja|寒露}} until the day before {{ill|Rittō|ja|立冬}}) as applicable.

== Days of Wuxu ==
The {{ill|Day Selection|ja|選日|1=Senjitsu}} for a Wuxu day is as follows.
=== Day Selection ===
A Wuxu day is the 6th day of {{ill|Ten Heaven, One Heaven|ja|天一天上}}.

