=== Events ===
* In the 9th year of {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|1838 AD|ja|1838th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), {{ill|Kōya Nagahide|ja|高野長英|qq=draft|qq=draft}} authored the work {{ill|Wuxu Dream Tale|ja|戊戌夢物語|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
* In the 24th year of {{ill|Guangxu|ja|光緒|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|1898 AD|ja|1898th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), during the Qing dynasty, reforms and political upheaval known as the {{ill|Wuxu Reform|ja|戊戌の変法|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and the {{ill|Wuxu Coup|ja|戊戌の政変|qq=draft|qq=draft}} took place.

== Months of Wuxu ==
In a {{ill|Common Era|ja|西暦|1=Common Era|2=ja|3=西暦|4=zh|5=公元|6=es|7=Era común|8=nl|9=Gangbare jaartelling|10=simple|11=Common Era|qq=draft|qq=draft}} year whose final digit is 1 or 6 (i.e. when the Ten Heavenly Stems are {{ill|Xin|ja|辛|1=Kanoto (辛)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} or {{ill|Bing|ja|丙|1=Hinoe (丙)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), the month of {{ill|September|ja|9月|qq=draft|qq=draft}} becomes the {{ill|Month (Calendar)|ja|月 (暦)|lt=Month|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of Wuxu. However, the term “month” here may refer either to the month of the {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft}} or to a seasonal month (from {{ill|Hanro|ja|寒露|qq=draft|qq=draft}} until the day before {{ill|Rittō|ja|立冬|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) as applicable.

== Days of Wuxu ==
The {{ill|Day Selection|ja|選日|1=Senjitsu|qq=draft|qq=draft}} for a Wuxu day is as follows.
=== Day Selection ===
A Wuxu day is the 6th day of {{ill|Ten Heaven, One Heaven|ja|天一天上|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
