In a {{ill|Common Era|ja|西暦|1=Common Era|2=ja|3=西暦|4=zh|5=公元|6=es|7=Era común|8=nl|9=Gangbare jaartelling|10=simple|11=Common Era|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} year whose final digit is 1 or 6 (i.e. when the Ten Heavenly Stems are {{ill|Xin|ja|辛|1=Kanoto (辛)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} or {{ill|Bing|ja|丙|1=Hinoe (丙)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}), the month of {{ill|September|ja|9月|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} becomes the {{ill|Month (Calendar)|ja|月 (暦)|lt=Month|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} of Wuxu. However, the term “month” here may refer either to the month of the {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} or to a seasonal month (from {{ill|Hanro|ja|寒露|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} until the day before {{ill|Rittō|ja|立冬|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}) as applicable.

== Days of Wuxu ==
The {{ill|Day Selection|ja|選日|1=Senjitsu|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} for a Wuxu day is as follows.
=== Day Selection ===
A Wuxu day is the 6th day of {{ill|Ten Heaven, One Heaven|ja|天一天上|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}.
